<topic id="text-view-JSON">
  <title>Editing JSON Documents in Text Mode</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>JSON documents<indexterm>Text mode editing features</indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p>When editing JSON documents in the <uicontrol>Text</uicontrol> editing mode, the <xref
        href="word-line-actions.dita#word-line-actions">usual text editing actions</xref> are
      available, along with other editor specific actions, including:<ul>
        <li><xref href="finding-replacing-text.dita#finding-replacing-text">Find /
          Replace</xref></li>
        <li><xref href="drag-and-drop-selected-text.dita#drag-and-drop-selected-text">Drag and
            Drop</xref></li>
        <li><xref href="validating-JSON.dita">Validation</xref></li>
        <li><xref href="format-and-indent-xml.dita#format-and-indent-xml">Format and Indent (Pretty
            Print)</xref></li>
      </ul></p>
    <p>
      <note>You can run XPath expressions on opened JSON documents, but in
          <uicontrol>Text</uicontrol> mode the XPath results cannot be mapped in the document.
        However, they can be mapped in the <uicontrol>Grid</uicontrol> editing mode. You can use the
          <uicontrol>Grid</uicontrol> button at the bottom of the editor panel to switch to that
        editing mode.</note>
    </p>
    <p>
      <fig>
